<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFF3563EFF1DD3B2FDD803F6" blockId="17.[165,794,930,1218]" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF3563EFF1DD3B2FC8D04CB" bold="true" box="[166,230,930,954]" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF3563EFF48D3B3FDE704CB" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[243,396,931,954]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF3563EFF48D3B3FDE704CB" box="[243,396,931,954]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">Bama gressitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles other dark-coloured 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF3563EFD60D3B3FF7204CB" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" box="[731,793,931,954]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF3563EFD60D3B3FF7204CB" box="[731,793,931,954]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">Bama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with the wing area in front of vein 3 extensively darkened (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF3563EFEE9D3CEFDD60484" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[338,445,989,1013]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexifer">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF3563EFEE9D3CEFDD60484" box="[338,445,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">B. flexifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), though the male only has the distal part curiously variegated (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFF3563EFDBBD3EAFE3B0363" box="[512,592,1018,1042]" captionStart="Figures 23–26" captionStartId="16.[357,429,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[357,1186,151,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-9@16.[357,1186,151,1668]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 23–26. Bama gressitti n.sp. (23) Left wing of male. (24) Left wing of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). The slight brown suffusion around the distal part of vein 5, the straight discal crossvein and the dark palpus aid specific identification, while such deeply divided male sternite 4 is so far otherwise known only in 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF3563EFEFCD460FDC703F6" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[327,428,1135,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickeli">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF3563EFEFCD460FDC703F6" box="[327,428,1135,1159]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">B. bickeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFF3563EFF7ED49DFEF303B3" blockId="17.[165,794,930,1218]" pageId="17" pageNumber="41">The specific epithet refers to the collector J. Linsley Gressitt, formerly of the B.P. Bishop Museum.</paragraph>
